-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Tue Dec 09, 2014 06:00AM EST
-- None



Dec 9 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1100 GMT on Tuesday:

** Canadian oil producer Talisman Energy Inc <TLM.TO> said it had been approached by a number of parties, including Spain's Repsol SA <REP.MC>, for various transactions. [ID:nL1N0TT041]  ** Heavily indebted Indonesian state-owned carrier PT Merpati Nusantara Airlines is exploring restructuring options including a debt-to-equity swap and finding strategic investors, its chief executive told Reuters. [ID:nL3N0TT1MX]  ** Britain's Land Securities Group Plc <LAND.L> has sold Scottish real estate worth 224.1 million pounds ($350.9 million) to HSBC Holdings Plc <HSBA.L> as it focuses on larger commercial property assets in and around London. [ID:nL6N0TT0Q4]  ** Dutch pharmaceuticals wholesaler Brocacef said that it was taking over businesses of Mediq, a medical supplies and equipment provider, to create a company with combined sales of 2.1 billion euros ($2.59 billion). [ID:nL6N0TT1AZ]  ** Private equity firm Carlyle Group LP <CG.O> said it bought a majority stake in India's Newgen KnowledgeWorks, a provider of publishing and technical services, for $32.8 million. [ID:nL3N0TT2PJ]